WEBVTT

00:02.603 --> 00:03.837
Previously on Empire...

00:03.871 --> 00:04.872
ANIKA: You think
that someone pushed you?

00:04.905 --> 00:06.006
RHONDA:
I really don't know.

00:06.040 --> 00:07.741
Freda, did you say something
about Frank Gathers?

00:07.775 --> 00:08.876
Yeah, that's my father.

00:08.909 --> 00:10.244
He got murdered in prison.

00:10.278 --> 00:12.646
The Lyon family
will be performing

00:12.680 --> 00:15.083
at this year's ASA awards.

00:15.116 --> 00:16.484
Jamal,

00:16.517 --> 00:18.386
you know D-Major,
musical director

00:18.419 --> 00:19.820
for the ASAs.
JAMAL: Of course.

00:19.853 --> 00:20.888
D-MAJOR:
I try to keep things
professional, man.

00:20.921 --> 00:22.256
And because you're not out.

00:22.290 --> 00:23.557
You know I don't want
to make you do anything

00:23.591 --> 00:24.758
you don't feel comfortable with.

00:24.792 --> 00:26.327
Tiana's doing a duet
with you on a song

00:26.360 --> 00:27.761
you yourself told me
would go platinum.

00:27.795 --> 00:28.896
The producers wanted her.

00:28.929 --> 00:30.064
I bet you never
even brought me up.

00:30.098 --> 00:31.765
If it was me,
I'd be jealous.

00:31.799 --> 00:33.667
If my sister had everything
and I had nothing.

00:33.701 --> 00:35.103
CAROL: You know, I'm about
to get my 90-day chip.

00:35.136 --> 00:36.570
Carol.
Tariq?

00:36.604 --> 00:38.339
So, what, you working
for the NYPD?

00:38.372 --> 00:41.109
No, I quit the force
a long time ago.

00:41.142 --> 00:42.510
COOKIE:
Lucious, who is this lady?

00:42.543 --> 00:44.445
This is Leah Walker,
Lucious' mother.

00:44.478 --> 00:47.181
COOKIE:
She's just a little, old lady,

00:47.215 --> 00:48.782
and there is
nothing to fear.

00:48.816 --> 00:51.419
I'm sorry I was too weak

00:51.452 --> 00:53.221
to kill you
when I had the chance.

00:55.489 --> 00:57.958
Now, tomorrow's the ASAs,
and this song

00:57.991 --> 01:01.395
has to be the highlight
of the show.

01:01.429 --> 01:04.198
I want the entire world
talking about it, okay?

01:04.232 --> 01:05.999
Bring us in.

01:07.435 --> 01:08.369
Stop, stop, stop, stop,

01:08.402 --> 01:10.037
you're too tentative
on the entrance.

01:10.070 --> 01:11.539
You know what?
Start again.

01:11.572 --> 01:13.073
(drummer plays intro)

01:13.107 --> 01:15.409
(band joins in)

01:15.443 --> 01:17.044
Stop. Remember

01:17.077 --> 01:18.646
it's a lullaby.
Look, we're gonna be here

01:18.679 --> 01:20.080
all night until
you get this right.

01:20.114 --> 01:21.649
Okay, start one more time.

01:21.682 --> 01:24.051
Two, three, four.

01:24.084 --> 01:25.286
(band playing)

01:29.257 --> 01:30.591
No, no.

01:30.624 --> 01:32.893
I want the strings
to come in just like that.

01:32.926 --> 01:34.094
Let's try that again.

01:34.128 --> 01:35.929
That chord, uh...

01:37.298 --> 01:40.568
(Lucious vocalizing with piano)

01:40.601 --> 01:41.835
No, tired is not an option.

01:41.869 --> 01:44.905
Get it together.

01:44.938 --> 01:46.607
Bring me back in one more time.

01:47.941 --> 01:50.411
Stop for a second.
Just give me... g-give me

01:50.444 --> 01:51.745
drums and give me bass.

01:51.779 --> 01:52.746
That pace...

01:52.780 --> 01:54.114
that's where we need to be at.

01:54.148 --> 01:56.850
Stop. We're getting there.

01:56.884 --> 01:57.851
We're getting there.

01:57.885 --> 01:59.287
Bring me back in.

01:59.320 --> 02:00.754
Make sure it's strong.

02:00.788 --> 02:01.922
There's no room for error.

02:01.955 --> 02:03.257
Yeah.

02:03.291 --> 02:04.758
This is the ASAs.

02:04.792 --> 02:07.595
(Lucious vocalizing)

02:07.628 --> 02:08.696
I like that, keep going.

02:08.729 --> 02:11.131
(Lucious vocalizing)

02:16.170 --> 02:17.805
Take us there.

02:17.838 --> 02:19.707
Yeah.

02:19.740 --> 02:21.675
Bass, yeah, keep going.

02:23.744 --> 02:25.779
I'm liking this a lot.

02:25.813 --> 02:28.148
Yeah.

02:28.182 --> 02:29.650
(band plays harmoniously)

02:41.829 --> 02:42.896
Give me a couple
minutes here.
Yes.

02:42.930 --> 02:45.165
You guys sound amazing.

02:45.199 --> 02:46.634
Band sounds
great, Lucious.

02:46.667 --> 02:47.901
Thanks, Cook.

02:47.935 --> 02:49.237
They're getting there.
What's up?

02:49.270 --> 02:51.472
How's your mama?

02:51.505 --> 02:52.973
She's still crazy.

02:53.006 --> 02:54.141
She's still
at your house, right?

02:54.174 --> 02:55.175
Yeah.

02:55.209 --> 02:56.744
Mm-hmm.
What's up?

02:56.777 --> 02:58.011
Um, Lucious, look,
I need you to get some rest.

02:58.045 --> 02:59.146
You've been at
this all night.

02:59.179 --> 03:00.147
Give the band a break.

03:00.180 --> 03:01.415
I'll rest when I'm dead,

03:01.449 --> 03:03.150
but right now we got
the ASAs tomorrow,

03:03.183 --> 03:04.652
and they got to be airtight.

03:04.685 --> 03:06.153
You know that this ain't
about the ASAs.

03:06.186 --> 03:08.088
This is about you
avoiding your mother.

03:08.121 --> 03:09.690
Why you letting that woman

03:09.723 --> 03:10.991
do this to you?

03:11.024 --> 03:12.660
Look, stay in
your lane, Cookie.

03:12.693 --> 03:14.262
Hey, Lucious, come here.

03:14.295 --> 03:15.596
Lucious...

03:15.629 --> 03:16.764
you're working yourself

03:16.797 --> 03:18.666
so hard so you can avoid.

03:18.699 --> 03:20.200
You have
to deal with this.

03:20.234 --> 03:21.869
Look, you didn't
go home last night.

03:21.902 --> 03:23.837
The other night you stayed
in your office.

03:23.871 --> 03:26.840
I told you,
the woman's dangerous,

03:26.874 --> 03:28.041
and I don't trust her.

03:28.075 --> 03:30.110
All right?

03:30.143 --> 03:32.179
Can I get back
to work, please?

03:32.212 --> 03:33.514
All right, Lucious.

03:33.547 --> 03:36.216
All right, count us
back in, sweetheart.

03:41.889 --> 03:43.291
FEMALE REPORTER:
We are one day away

03:43.324 --> 03:46.193
from the 54th Annual
American Sound Awards.

03:46.226 --> 03:49.029
The big question
everybody is asking:

03:49.062 --> 03:50.197
which Lyon will come...

03:50.230 --> 03:52.232
ANNOUNCER: Tomorrow night
on Fox, the 54th...

03:52.266 --> 03:54.468
WEATHERMAN:
The rain is supposed to clear up
for tomorrow, so it should be...

03:54.502 --> 03:56.069
Ms. Walker.

03:56.103 --> 04:01.409
Toast, ham, scrambled eggs,
everything you like.

04:01.442 --> 04:03.210
No. Seasoning.

04:03.243 --> 04:04.545
Pardon me?

04:04.578 --> 04:05.813
You don't season your food.

04:05.846 --> 04:07.481
I'm not eating it.

04:07.515 --> 04:08.916
Just give me coffee.

04:08.949 --> 04:10.551
...covering the red carpet.

04:10.584 --> 04:11.585
Forecast earlier...

04:11.619 --> 04:12.720
MAN:
It's an honor to be nominated--

04:12.753 --> 04:14.388
I mean, a big honor--

04:14.422 --> 04:16.223
and I'm really exci...

04:16.256 --> 04:17.558
(cheering on television)

04:17.591 --> 04:18.926
I thought I fired you.

04:18.959 --> 04:19.927
Hmm.

04:19.960 --> 04:21.495
WOMAN:
Katy Perry, Taylor Swift.

04:21.529 --> 04:23.831
WOMAN 2:
Ah, well, I can't wait
to see what Taylor Swift...

04:23.864 --> 04:25.333
FEMALE REPORTER:
In the video for his nominated

04:25.366 --> 04:26.900
hit song,
"Boom Boom Boom Boom,"

04:26.934 --> 04:28.336
Lucious Lyon shares

04:28.369 --> 04:30.070
a heartbreaking story about his

04:30.103 --> 04:32.072
bipolar mother
who took her own life.

04:32.105 --> 04:33.841
It's a rare look inside

04:33.874 --> 04:35.343
one man's very
personal journey

04:35.376 --> 04:37.345
through pain and poverty.

04:37.378 --> 04:39.079
Lucious Lyon's
own journey this year

04:39.112 --> 04:41.349
has been remarkable,
having served

04:41.382 --> 04:43.183
three months in prison
for what many

04:43.216 --> 04:45.085
consider a racially
motivated prosecution,

04:45.118 --> 04:46.420
and then losing

04:46.454 --> 04:47.421
and regaining control

04:47.455 --> 04:49.256
of his Empire Entertainment,

04:49.289 --> 04:50.358
only to emerge with...

04:50.391 --> 04:52.626
Boom.

04:52.660 --> 04:53.861
...one of the biggest
hits of his career.

04:53.894 --> 04:55.796
* Bang, bang, bang, bang

04:55.829 --> 04:56.930
* Boom, boom, boom, boom

04:56.964 --> 04:58.366
Boom.

04:58.399 --> 05:00.768
* Bang, bang, bang, bang
Boom.

05:00.801 --> 05:05.639
He's always been a liar.

05:05.673 --> 05:08.442
A bald-faced liar.

05:08.476 --> 05:11.111
