05:18.151 --> 05:19.286
Thank you, William.
Okay.

05:19.319 --> 05:21.455
Hey, Cook, look, Rhonda
just fit me in this dress.

05:21.489 --> 05:23.791
It's banging, right?

05:23.824 --> 05:24.825
So what do you think

05:24.858 --> 05:26.394
about me wearing
it to the ASAs?

05:26.427 --> 05:29.129
Thanks. Sure, but not
if you're going with me.

05:29.162 --> 05:30.631
You need to tell Rhonda
to get you something

05:30.664 --> 05:31.899
a little more appropriate.

05:31.932 --> 05:33.801
You look like a cheap

05:33.834 --> 05:35.302
prostitute.

05:35.335 --> 05:37.838
So what skank you think
Lucious is taking?

05:37.871 --> 05:40.808
Girl, I don't know,
and I don't care.

05:40.841 --> 05:42.976
All I care about is getting
those boys up on that stage,

05:43.010 --> 05:45.646
because come Sunday,
all the headlines

05:45.679 --> 05:48.148
are gonna be calling us
"The First Family of Hip Hop,"

05:48.181 --> 05:49.817
and that is all I care about.

05:49.850 --> 05:51.852
Girl, guess who I ran
into at the restaurant

05:51.885 --> 05:54.254
on Great Jones Street.

05:54.287 --> 05:56.356
Tariq Cousins,
remember him?

05:56.390 --> 05:57.758
Fine-ass Tariq?

05:57.791 --> 05:59.693
Tariq the Freak?
Yeah.

05:59.727 --> 06:01.529
The cop?
No, no...

06:01.562 --> 06:03.831
he's not working
for the Philly PD anymore.

06:03.864 --> 06:04.932
He lives here
in New York.

06:04.965 --> 06:06.333
(phone chimes)
Girl...

06:06.366 --> 06:08.502
he just invited me
to dinner at Laviticus.

06:08.536 --> 06:10.504
Ooh, you know,
I'm gonna ask Rhonda

06:10.538 --> 06:11.705
if I could borrow this dress

06:11.739 --> 06:14.041
just in case Tariq
wants to freak!

06:14.074 --> 06:15.943
Yes, Tariq!

06:15.976 --> 06:18.378
(sighs)

