I know, wow.

07:33.954 --> 07:34.922
Thank you.

07:34.955 --> 07:36.189
Oh, no, no, no, no,

07:36.223 --> 07:37.257
the two of y'all did that.

07:37.290 --> 07:38.926
For real, you got magic.

07:38.959 --> 07:40.861
Thank you.
Oh!

07:40.894 --> 07:42.129
We can't lose it!

07:42.162 --> 07:43.764
That's magic.
That's what's up, right?

07:43.797 --> 07:45.799
Right, look, I'm-a get back
to the shop, cut some heads.

07:45.833 --> 07:47.434
Yeah.
D-Major, man,

07:47.467 --> 07:48.602
I appreciate it;
it's a pleasure.

07:48.636 --> 07:49.603
All right.

07:49.637 --> 07:50.771
I'll catch y'all later.

07:50.804 --> 07:51.805
All right, Freda.
All right.

07:53.507 --> 07:55.308
(elevator bell dings)

07:55.342 --> 07:59.479
J... it's time
to let your mom go.

08:02.482 --> 08:03.617
You ain't serious?

08:03.651 --> 08:04.652
I'm dead-ass.

08:04.685 --> 08:06.620
Hell no, Derek.

08:06.654 --> 08:07.721
That's my mother,

08:07.755 --> 08:09.456
and-and besides,
I love working with her.

08:09.489 --> 08:11.458
She's producing the whole damn
Black and White album.

08:11.491 --> 08:12.826
Jamal...

08:12.860 --> 08:14.562
you're so much
bigger than whatever

08:14.595 --> 08:16.797
your moms and pops could do
for your sound right now.

08:16.830 --> 08:18.966
Plus they keep you twisted up.

08:18.999 --> 08:20.233
It's time for
you to be more

08:20.267 --> 08:22.469
than a musical
mama's boy.

08:22.502 --> 08:23.804
You should level up.

08:23.837 --> 08:26.540
Let me produce your next album.

08:28.609 --> 08:30.077
You want to produce
my next album?

08:30.110 --> 08:32.479
Yeah.

08:32.512 --> 08:35.348
Unless I ain't
big enough for you.

08:37.017 --> 08:39.753
Party with disguises.

08:39.787 --> 08:40.821
Ten letters.

08:40.854 --> 08:42.656
You tell me.

08:42.690 --> 08:44.524
Masked ball.

08:44.558 --> 08:45.793
(chuckles)

08:47.961 --> 08:49.763
So, you good, Grandma?

08:49.797 --> 08:50.831
Are you eating right?

08:50.864 --> 08:51.999
You taking your medication?

08:52.032 --> 08:53.934
So many pills, make me choke.

08:53.967 --> 08:56.203
Why can't they put
it all in one?

08:56.236 --> 08:58.205
But you feel
better, right?

08:58.238 --> 09:01.274
Do the staff take you out
to get some fresh air?

09:01.308 --> 09:03.611
So many maids and people
working in this house,

09:03.644 --> 09:05.045
it feels like
Gone with the Wind.

09:05.078 --> 09:08.415
But everybody treats you
respectfully, right?

09:10.383 --> 09:12.019
I don't like being left out.

09:12.052 --> 09:13.520
Left out, how?

09:13.553 --> 09:15.355
They talk about
it on the TV,

09:15.388 --> 09:17.324
and I know Dwight's
gonna be in it.

09:19.727 --> 09:21.194
You talking
about the ASAs?

09:21.228 --> 09:23.030
They said my whole
family's performing,

09:23.063 --> 09:24.231
but nobody invited me.

09:24.264 --> 09:25.699
Do you know

09:25.733 --> 09:28.368
I've never even
seen him on a stage?

09:28.401 --> 09:31.371
Lucious Lyon.

09:31.404 --> 09:35.308
Look, I'd-I'd love to
take you to the ASAs, Grandma.

09:35.342 --> 09:38.879
I'd need to talk
to Empire's PR department

09:38.912 --> 09:40.480
to see if we can even
get an extra ticket.

09:40.513 --> 09:41.915
Tell Dwight
to talk to them.

09:41.949 --> 09:43.250
He can get me a ticket.

09:43.283 --> 09:45.218
(sighs)
You'd need a new dress...

09:45.252 --> 09:47.487
and I would have to

09:47.520 --> 09:49.556
run it by Pop. It could be
a tricky situation.

09:49.589 --> 09:51.491
Because he wishes I was dead.

09:51.524 --> 09:52.826
Grandma, he doesn't
wish that you were...

09:52.860 --> 09:54.227
That's what he
told everybody

09:54.261 --> 09:55.328
in that movie he made.

09:55.362 --> 09:56.730
That was just a movie.

09:56.764 --> 09:58.732
Okay, it was a story,
make-believe.

09:58.766 --> 09:59.767
Now, the problem...

09:59.800 --> 10:01.434
I won't tell anybody he lied,

10:01.468 --> 10:04.571
if that's what you're scared of.

10:04.604 --> 10:06.674
I just want to see
my grandbabies up there

10:06.707 --> 10:08.241
on that stage, that's all.

10:08.275 --> 10:09.910
It would destroy
his credibility

10:09.943 --> 10:12.245
if anybody found
out, Grandma.

10:12.279 --> 10:14.081
It'd be bad for Empire,
and it would be

10:14.114 --> 10:16.083
really, really bad for Pop.

10:16.116 --> 10:20.520
Honey, there's gonna be
so many pretty girls there,

10:20.553 --> 10:22.923
nobody's even
gonna look sideways

10:22.956 --> 10:25.325
at a little old lady.

10:44.912 --> 10:46.947
Hey, Rhonda.

10:46.980 --> 10:48.448
Hey.
Oh, hey.

10:48.481 --> 10:49.783
Sorry, do you
have a minute?

10:49.817 --> 10:52.285
Well, I'm on my way
to a fitting for a bunch

10:52.319 --> 10:54.321
of artists for
the ASAs, uh, well...

10:54.354 --> 10:56.323
I'll meet you guys there,
just go ahead without me.
Sure.

10:56.356 --> 10:57.390
Hey, sorry.

10:57.424 --> 10:58.391
Sorry, I barely
have a minute.

10:58.425 --> 10:59.827
What's up?
Um...

10:59.860 --> 11:02.462
You weren't at yoga
the other day and, uh,

11:02.495 --> 11:04.297
I thought I'd see you there,
and I've been texting you,

11:04.331 --> 11:05.465
and it's just not like you
to not respond, so...

11:05.498 --> 11:06.834
I've just been crazed

11:06.867 --> 11:08.301
dressing all these artists,
that's all.

11:08.335 --> 11:11.204
Oh, okay.

11:13.006 --> 11:15.308
Oh.

11:15.342 --> 11:17.677
Oh, my God,
I'm starting to show,

11:17.711 --> 11:19.813
and it's painful for you,
I'm sorry, Rhonda.

11:19.847 --> 11:21.348
No.
I'm so stupid.

11:21.381 --> 11:22.750
No, no, Anika.
I should be
more sensitive.

11:22.783 --> 11:23.751
I'm fine, honestly.

11:23.784 --> 11:24.918
